(secondQuint)SeRenade Parent-Child Music Class Program.

 This pilot study evaluates the impact of the SeRenade Parent-Child Music Class Program on families of children with and without autism spectrum disorders (ASD).

 This study examines the impact of this program on social development in children with ASD, parental stress and efficacy, and parent-child relationships.

 A primary goal of this study is to examine multiple levels of analysis including families' experience within and outside of the music class program.

